arkdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-st=
yling"><p data-start=3D"0" data-end=3D"180"><strong data-start=3D"0" data-e=
nd=3D"7">VVT</strong> stands for <strong data-start=3D"19" data-end=3D"44">=
Variable Valve Timing</strong>.<br data-start=3D"45" data-end=3D"48">
It is a technology in car engines that <strong data-start=3D"87" data-end=
=3D"151">changes when the intake and/or exhaust valves open and close</stro=
ng> while the engine is running.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"182" data-end=3D"185">
<h2 data-start=3D"187" data-end=3D"221">Why VVT exists (the basic idea)</h2=
>
<p data-start=3D"223" data-end=3D"289">An engine behaves differently at <st=
rong data-start=3D"256" data-end=3D"269">low speed</strong> and <strong dat=
a-start=3D"274" data-end=3D"288">high speed</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"291" data-end=3D"434">
<li data-start=3D"291" data-end=3D"371">
<p data-start=3D"293" data-end=3D"371">At <strong data-start=3D"296" data-e=
nd=3D"307">low RPM</strong> =E2=86=92 you want smooth idle, good torque, an=
d low fuel consumption</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"372" data-end=3D"434">
<p data-start=3D"374" data-end=3D"434">At <strong data-start=3D"377" data-e=
nd=3D"389">high RPM</strong> =E2=86=92 you want maximum air flow for higher=
 power</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"436" data-end=3D"559">With <strong data-start=3D"441" data=
-end=3D"463">fixed valve timing</strong>, the valve timing is a compromise.=
<br data-start=3D"498" data-end=3D"501">
<strong data-start=3D"501" data-end=3D"520">VVT solves this</strong> by adj=
usting valve timing dynamically.</p>
<hr data-start=3D"561" data-end=3D"564">
<h2 data-start=3D"566" data-end=3D"595">How VVT works (simplified)</h2>
<p data-start=3D"597" data-end=3D"613">In a VVT engine:</p>
<ol data-start=3D"615" data-end=3D"885">
<li data-start=3D"615" data-end=3D"670">
<p data-start=3D"618" data-end=3D"670">The <strong data-start=3D"622" data-=
end=3D"634">camshaft</strong> controls valve opening and closing.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"671" data-end=3D"739">
<p data-start=3D"674" data-end=3D"739">A <strong data-start=3D"676" data-en=
d=3D"705">VVT actuator (cam phaser)</strong> can rotate the camshaft slight=
ly.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"740" data-end=3D"885">
<p data-start=3D"743" data-end=3D"811">The <strong data-start=3D"747" data-=
end=3D"776">ECU (engine control unit)</strong> commands this adjustment bas=
ed on:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"815" data-end=3D"885">
<li data-start=3D"815" data-end=3D"835">
<p data-start=3D"817" data-end=3D"835">Engine speed (RPM)</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"839" data-end=3D"858">
<p data-start=3D"841" data-end=3D"858">Throttle position</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"862" data-end=3D"868">
<p data-start=3D"864" data-end=3D"868">Load</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"872" data-end=3D"885">
<p data-start=3D"874" data-end=3D"885">Temperature</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start=3D"887" data-end=3D"900">This changes:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"901" data-end=3D"1011">
<li data-start=3D"901" data-end=3D"923">
<p data-start=3D"903" data-end=3D"923">When valves <strong data-start=3D"91=
5" data-end=3D"923">open</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"924" data-end=3D"947">
<p data-start=3D"926" data-end=3D"947">When valves <strong data-start=3D"93=
8" data-end=3D"947">close</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"948" data-end=3D"1011">
<p data-start=3D"950" data-end=3D"1011">Sometimes <strong data-start=3D"960=
" data-end=3D"972">how long</strong> they stay open (with advanced systems)=
</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1013" data-end=3D"1016">
<h2 data-start=3D"1018" data-end=3D"1038">What VVT improves</h2>
<ul data-start=3D"1040" data-end=3D"1184">
<li data-start=3D"1040" data-end=3D"1068">
<p data-start=3D"1042" data-end=3D"1068">=E2=9C=85 Better fuel efficiency</=
p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1069" data-end=3D"1096">
<p data-start=3D"1071" data-end=3D"1096">=E2=9C=85 Higher low-RPM torque</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1097" data-end=3D"1122">
<p data-start=3D"1099" data-end=3D"1122">=E2=9C=85 More high-RPM power</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1123" data-end=3D"1152">
<p data-start=3D"1125" data-end=3D"1152">=E2=9C=85 Lower exhaust emissions<=
/p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1153" data-end=3D"1184">
<p data-start=3D"1155" data-end=3D"1184">=E2=9C=85 Smoother engine operatio=
n</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1186" data-end=3D"1189">
<h2 data-start=3D"1191" data-end=3D"1214">Types of VVT systems</h2>
<h3 data-start=3D"1216" data-end=3D"1256">1. <strong data-start=3D"1223" da=
ta-end=3D"1256">Cam-phasing VVT (most common)</strong></h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1257" data-end=3D"1336">
<li data-start=3D"1257" data-end=3D"1282">
<p data-start=3D"1259" data-end=3D"1282">Changes <strong data-start=3D"1267=
" data-end=3D"1282">timing only</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1283" data-end=3D"1313">
<p data-start=3D"1285" data-end=3D"1313">Valves open earlier or later</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1314" data-end=3D"1336">
<p data-start=3D"1316" data-end=3D"1336">Used in many engines</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1338" data-end=3D"1357">2. <strong data-start=3D"1345" da=
ta-end=3D"1357">Dual VVT</strong></h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1358" data-end=3D"1448">
<li data-start=3D"1358" data-end=3D"1406">
<p data-start=3D"1360" data-end=3D"1406">Controls <strong data-start=3D"136=
9" data-end=3D"1406">both intake and exhaust camshafts</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1407" data-end=3D"1448">
<p data-start=3D"1409" data-end=3D"1448">Better efficiency and emissions co=
ntrol</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start=3D"1450" data-end=3D"1489">3. <strong data-start=3D"1457" da=
ta-end=3D"1489">Variable Valve Lift &amp; Timing</strong></h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1490" data-end=3D"1569">
<li data-start=3D"1490" data-end=3D"1534">
<p data-start=3D"1492" data-end=3D"1534">Changes <strong data-start=3D"1500=
" data-end=3D"1534">timing AND how far valves open</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1535" data-end=3D"1569">
<p data-start=3D"1537" data-end=3D"1569">More complex, higher performance</=
p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1571" data-end=3D"1574">
<h2 data-start=3D"1576" data-end=3D"1612">Common VVT names by manufacturers=
</h2>
<p data-start=3D"1613" data-end=3D"1653">(Concept is the same, name is diff=
erent)</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1655" data-end=3D"1759">
<li data-start=3D"1655" data-end=3D"1671">
<p data-start=3D"1657" data-end=3D"1671">VVT-i (Toyota)</p>
